      • ExtensionArm

        public ExtensionArm​(edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.smartdashboard.MechanismLigament2d ligament)
        Initializes the extension arm and configures the necessary device settings. Motors are set to: Factory default, then given 9 volts of voltage compensation, and put in brake mode
        Parameters:
        ligament - the ligament object that is on smart-dashboard

    • Method Detail

      • periodic

        public void periodic()
        If the Arm is retracting and hits the limit switch we reset encoder's and we stop the arm from further retracting to prevent the motor from breaking the arm. We also need to check if the arm is at max extension. If so then we stop the motors. The ligament object on glass is also updated from here. If the extension arm isn't running at the current desired speed then spin the arm

      • extendArmTo

        public void extendArmTo​(double length)
        Updates currentSetpoint. Extends the arm to a passed in length. Uses motion magic. Should only be called once per routine. Constant updates will result in a jerky on-off output to the motor.
        Parameters:
        length - (ticks) to extend the arm to.

      • stop

        public void stop()
        Stops the arm.

      • dumbPower

      • brokeLimit

        public boolean brokeLimit()
        Uses the limit switch to see if we have broken it. Limit switch input is inverted (false is broken).
        Returns:
        Whether the extension arm is at the limit switch

      • updateValues

        public void updateValues()
        update values on shuffleboard. Values that are updated here are: P, I, and D values for the feedback controller.

      • spinExtensionArm

        public void spinExtensionArm​(double speed)
        spins the extension arm. calls getSmartSpeed(double) in order to apply soft limits. If we are in debug mode (based on Constants.debugMode) ten it updates the acceleration manager (accelerationManager).
        Parameters:
        speed - to run the motor at. Bounds: (-1 - 1) gets multiplied by Constants.kMaxExtensionArmVoltage and that is supplied to the motor.

      • resetEncoders

        public void resetEncoders()
        Reset the extension motor encoders

      • atPosition

        public boolean atPosition()
        Whether we are at the position or not in a dead band defined by positionDeadband
        Returns:
        whether the extension arm is at it's set position

      • extendArmToGround

        public void extendArmToGround()
        Extends the extension arm to the setpoint on the ground. Uses motion magic.
